    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a little drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until golden</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-creamy-chicken-thigh-pie-with-mash-and-roast-carrots/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>finely and chop the <strong>remaining carrot</strong> into batons</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-creamy-chicken-thigh-pie-with-mash-and-roast-carrots/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is golden, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>leek </strong>and <strong>diced</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> and cook for 3 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>with a small knob of <strong>butter </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-creamy-chicken-thigh-pie-with-mash-and-roast-carrots/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat, then cook for 2-3 min or until thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add your <strong>soft cheese</strong>,<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong>, then give everything a good mix up and set aside off the heat \u2013 this is your <strong>pie mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-creamy-chicken-thigh-pie-with-mash-and-roast-carrots/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> then score a cross in the middle</p><p>Transfer the <strong>pie mix</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish[es]</strong>, top with the pastry, then crimp the edges with a fork to seal the pastry to the dish</p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 20-25 min or until the pastry is puffed up and golden and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>classic creamy chicken pie</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-creamy-chicken-thigh-pie-with-mash-and-roast-carrots/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>carrot batons </strong>to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>(or two!) with a splash of <strong>cold water</strong>, a little drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and a small pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the carrot batons to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 18-20 min or until the carrots are tender</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-creamy-chicken-thigh-pie-with-mash-and-roast-carrots/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the carrots are cooking, reboil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>potatoes </strong>into small bite-sized pieces, then add<strong> </strong>the<strong> chopped potatoes </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p><p>Return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat and add a splash of <strong>milk </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper </strong>and mash until smooth</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-creamy-chicken-thigh-pie-with-mash-and-roast-carrots/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>classic creamy chicken pie </strong>with the <strong>mash </strong>and <strong>roast carrot</strong> to the side</p><p>Discard the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Loved this recipe? Keep an eye out for it on the Everyday Favourites section of our menu.</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
